result.execSummary:
The defendant Brandon Q Davis was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: PTAC], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Consec to any sentence currently serving.  Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.  Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

superMiscConds.notes: DA has 90 days to prepare/submit order.

$250 DNA surcharge remitted. $278  to be collected by the Dept of Corrections.  Court financial obligations shall be paid at the rate of 25% of the prison wages and work release funds.  Restitution shall be paid pursuant to separate court order.  The balance remaining at release from prison be paid as a condition of extended supervision or parole at a rate determined by the supervising agent.
Maintain full-time employment/education or combination of or be seeking same, and treatment.  Obtain GED or high school diploma or equivalency.
Defendant not to use or possess any weapon.

Defendant shall not use/possess drug paraphernalia and/or controlled substances without a valid prescription. If granted a valid prescription, def to inform his agent and take only as prescribed.  Maintain absolute sobriety.  Do not drive a motor vehicle without valid DL and approval of agent & valid insurance.  Defendant shall not have any contact, direct or indirect, with CC, TW or his family or residence. Not to hunt or fish without appropriate licenses and approval from the agent.

Participate in and successfully complete CGIP/Thinking for a change program as recommended.  Defendant shall complete a risk and needs assessment and comply with care plan goals related to prioritized need areas identified.  Any other conditions DOC, Probation/Parole Department may impose.
